title: Google\Cloud\Asset\V1\CreateSavedQueryRequest
name: CreateSavedQueryRequest
description:
Request to create a saved query.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.asset.v1.CreateSavedQueryRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The name of the project/folder/organization where this saved_query should be created in. It can only be an organization number (such as "organizations/123"), a folder number (such as "folders/123"), a project ID (such as "projects/my-project-id")", or a project number (such as "projects/12345").

params.name: data.saved_query
params.description: Required. The saved_query details. The name field must be empty as it will be generated based on the parent and saved_query_id.

params.name: data.saved_query_id
params.description: Required. The ID to use for the saved query, which must be unique in the specified parent. It will become the final component of the saved query's resource name. This value should be 4-63 characters, and valid characters are /[a-z][0-9]-/. Notice that this field is required in the saved query creation, and the name field of the saved_query will be ignored.
